        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 2:02PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 202 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 21
miles northeast of Clyde Park, or 29 miles northwest of Big Timber,
moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Melville.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
